22 August 2012The Inter-Ministerial Committee on the Marikana tragedy, led by Minister in The Presidency Collins Chabane working together with religious leaders, mine workers and other stakeholders, will be holding an official memorial service for victims of the Marikana tragedy.The memorial service will be conducted and led by the religious leadership. The memorial is expected to be attended by ministers, religious leaders, traditional leaders, mine workers and members of the community.The memorial service will be held as follows;DATE: 23 August 2012 VENUE: Nkaneng Informal Settlement TIME: 11h00Members of the media are requested to arrive at 10h00.Enquiries: Harold Maloka Cell: 082 847 9799 E-mail: maloka.harold@gmail.comIssued by the Inter-Ministerial Committee